# Hydra — Agent Rules

## Project
- Name: Hydra — Multi-GPU LLM inference with KV state management
- Languages: C# (.NET 10) for **Hydra.Core — the single service** (coordinator + store +
  session mgmt, merged via PR #203) | Python only for system/E2E tests (`tests/`)
- The Python coordinator is **DEPRECATED/removed**. `src/coordinator/` is historical
  reference only — never extend it; all new service code goes in `src/core/Hydra.Core`.

## Architecture — One Protocol Rule
Hydra.Core is one binary: HTTP API :9000, Store RPC :9500, metrics :9501.
It talks to llama-servers directly: HTTP for completions, Hydra binary RPC (TCP) for
KV state ops (StateGet/StatePut on llama RPC ports :9503/:9502). There are no separate
Agent or Coordinator services/containers.
HTTP ONLY at edges: Client→Hydra.Core and Hydra.Core→llama-server completions.

## C# Rules (Hydra.Core)
- System.IO.Pipelines for ALL RPC protocol parsing — never manual byte arrays
- Socket.SendFileAsync for zero-copy file transfer from tmpfs
- BinaryPrimitives for all LE integer read/write
- Records for immutable data, sealed classes for services
- ILogger<T> everywhere, Serilog JSON formatter
- xUnit + Moq for testing
- NativeAOT-compatible: no dynamic reflection, no unbound generics at runtime
- appsettings.json + IConfiguration for config (no hardcoded values)
- Never buffer full 800 MB in memory — stream via PipeReader/PipeWriter

## Python Rules (system/E2E tests only — no Python service code)
- asyncio only — no threading, no multiprocessing
- httpx (async) for all HTTP calls
- pytest + `@pytest.mark.system` for tests requiring live services
- Never buffer full state in memory — stream chunk-by-chunk

## Critical SSM Constraint
NEVER send a request where n_tokens ≤ n_past to a restored slot.
SSM truncation is broken on qwen35moe. Hydra.Core MUST guard this (n_past guard).

## Logging
Every log line MUST include: ts, level, component, trace_id, event.
trace_id flows through every hop: Client → Hydra.Core → llama RPC / Store RPC.

## Before Writing Code
1. Read relevant docs/ and specs/ for the task
2. Output execution plan (files to create/modify)
3. Wait for confirmation
